Quote: The prosperity is assigned to two causes;  first that Canterbury has put in practice the Wakefield theory of a "sufficient price" for the land, alienating none at a less price than aGBP2 per acre, while other Provinces have parted with their estates to capitalists and speculators at 10s and 5s per acre.
